      "text": "In ancient Greece an ekklesiasterion was a building specifically built for the purpose of holding the supreme meetings of the ecclesia. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "45589b36449b159a",
      "text": "Like many other cities Athens did not have an ekklesiasterion. Instead, the regular meetings of the assembly were held on the [[Pnyx]] and two annual meetings took place in the [[Theater of Dionysus]]."
    },
